# Component Structure

The application uses a modular component architecture with specialized component directories.

## Component Categories

- [src/components/ui](mdc:src/components/ui) - Base UI components (shadcn/ui)
- [src/components/navigation](mdc:src/components/navigation) - Navigation components (sidebar, navbar)
- [src/components/layouts](mdc:src/components/layouts) - Layout components and containers
- [src/components/canvas](mdc:src/components/canvas) - Canvas-related components for drawing/visualization
- [src/components/common](mdc:src/components/common) - Shared components used across the application
- [src/components/settings](mdc:src/components/settings) - Settings-related components
- [src/components/journey](mdc:src/components/journey) - Learning journey components
- [src/components/achievements](mdc:src/components/achievements) - Achievement-related components
- [src/components/icons](mdc:src/components/icons) - Custom icon components

## Component Usage Guidelines

1. Use the appropriate component category for new components
2. Reuse existing components when possible
3. Follow the established coding patterns for props and state management
4. Maintain consistent styling with Tailwind classes